---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";

import ProjectHeader from "../../components/ProjectHeader.astro";
import SmallHeading from "../../components/SmallHeading.astro";
import Link from "../../components/Link.astro";
import Microcopy from "../../components/Microcopy.astro";
import Caption from "../../components/Caption.astro";
import ProjectGrid from "../../components/ProjectGrid.astro";

import italianAlps from "../../images/glaciers/italian-alps.png";
import world from "../../images/glaciers/world.gif";
import gulkana from "../../images/glaciers/gulkana.gif";
import lemonCreek from "../../images/glaciers/lemon-creek.gif";
import wolverine from "../../images/glaciers/wolverine.gif";
import southCascade from "../../images/glaciers/south-cascade.gif";
import glaciers from "../../images/glaciers/glaciers.gif";

import videoHero from "../../images/glaciers/witnessing_glaciers.mp4";
import videoHeroPoster from "../../images/glaciers/witnessing_glaciers-poster.jpg";
import videoStudy from "../../images/glaciers/a_dangerously_unscientific_study_on_glaciers_and_sea_level.mp4";
import videoStudyPoster from "../../images/glaciers/a_dangerously_unscientific_study_on_glaciers_and_sea_level-poster.jpg";

import webpage1 from "../../images/glaciers/webpage1.png";
import webpage2 from "../../images/glaciers/webpage2.png";
import webpage3 from "../../images/glaciers/webpage3.png";
import webpage4 from "../../images/glaciers/webpage4.png";
import FrameCaption from "../../components/FrameCaption.astro"
---

<Layout title="Brian Sekelsky">
  <main>
    <ProjectHeader
      title="Witnessing Glaciers"
      objective="This project came out of a workshop taught by Scott Reinhard, a graphics designer at The New York Times. The brief was to work as both journalist and designer, picking an issue, finding real data, and presenting it in an engaging way. I chose the impact of climate change on the world's glaciers, working with data from the World Glacier Monitoring Service (WGMS)."
      types={["Website", "Research", "Data-driven"]}
      collaborators={[]}
      year="2022"
      heroVideoMp4={videoHero}
      heroPoster={videoHeroPoster.src}
    />
    <ProjectGrid>
        <div class="col-span-1">
          <SmallHeading text="Process" />
          <p>
            I started with background research on glaciers, first focusing on the Alps and then widening out to the whole world. The turning point was finding the <Link
            name="World Glacier Monitoring Service's database,"
            href="https://wgms.ch/"
          /> which tracks the size and mass of glaciers worldwide over time. Once I had the data, I started sketching ways to present it.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-1">
          <Image
            class="shadow-sm w-3/4 mx-auto"
            src={italianAlps}
            alt="Research collection in Figma showing Alps imagery and data graphics"
          />
          <Caption text="Collecting research in Figma" />
        </div>
        <!--////////////////////////////-->
        <div class="col-span-1">
          <p>
            In Processing, I coded animations showing how quickly glaciers around the world are shrinking. The WGMS dataset also highlights a set of "benchmark glaciers," which are heavily monitored and stand in for global glacier trends.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-1">
          <div class="relative">
            <Image
              class="shadow-sm"
              src={world}
              alt="Data visualization showing global glacier shrinkage over time"
            />
            <FrameCaption text="First Processing sketch" />
          </div>
        </div>
        <!--////////////////////////////-->
        <div class="col-span-1">
          <Image
            class=""
            src={gulkana}
            alt="Gulkana glacier visualization as shrinking wireframe cube"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-1">
          <Image
            class=""
            src={wolverine}
            alt="Wolverine glacier visualization as shrinking wireframe cube"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-1">
          <Image
            class=""
            src={lemonCreek}
            alt="Lemon Creek glacier visualization as shrinking wireframe cube"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-1">
          <Image
            class=""
            src={southCascade}
            alt="South Cascade glacier visualization as shrinking wireframe cube"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-1">
          <p>
            Alongside the data work, I ran looser studies to spark ideas. One of them stuck. I converted the glacier data into MIDI notes and played them through a synthesizer. The sounds came out ancient and otherworldly, and they set the art direction for the final website.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-1 relative">
          <video playsinline autoplay muted loop preload="metadata" poster={videoStudyPoster.src}>
            <source src={videoStudy} type="video/mp4" />
          </video>
          <FrameCaption text="A dangerously unscientific study on glaciers and sea level" />
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-1">
          <SmallHeading text="The website" />
          <p>
          The final piece is an interactive scrollytelling website. Using Three.js, I built a 3D model of the Earth and mapped all the world's glaciers from the WGMS database onto the sphere. As you scroll, the camera moves around the globe, zooming in on key glaciers and narrating their decline. The site turns the dataset into a story you can explore, one glacier at a time.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-1">
          <Image class="shadow-sm" src={webpage1} alt="Witnessing Glaciers website hero section" />
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-2">
          <Image class="shadow-sm" src={webpage2} alt="Interactive globe showing glacier locations" />
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-2">
          <Image class="shadow-sm" src={webpage3} alt="Glacier data visualization detail view" />
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-2">
          <Image class="shadow-sm" src={webpage4} alt="Scrollytelling narrative section" />
        </div>
      </ProjectGrid>
  </main>
</Layout>
